<div class="container">
  <p>
    Hummus is a delicious and nutritious food that is enjoyed by many people around the world. It is made from chickpeas, tahini, olive oil, lemon juice, and garlic. Hummus is a great source of protein, fiber, and healthy fats. It is also low in calories and can be enjoyed as a snack or a meal. There are many different types of hummus available, including traditional, roasted red pepper, and garlic. Hummus is a versatile food that can be enjoyed in many different ways, such as with pita bread, vegetables, or as a spread on sandwiches. If you are looking for a healthy and delicious snack, hummus is a great choice!
  </p>

  <p> 
    If you are a hummus lover, you have come to the right place! Here you will find a list of all the different types of hummus available, including their retail price, serving size, and brand name. Whether you are looking for a traditional hummus or a more exotic flavor, you are sure to find something that you will love. So go ahead and explore the world of hummus and discover all the delicious options that are available to you!
  </p>

  <p>
    You can also create an account and log in to save your favorite hummus types. So what are you waiting for? Start exploring the world of hummus today and discover all the delicious options that are available to you!
  </p>
</div>
<!-- This is the main content of the page -->
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Hummus List</h2>
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Hummus Name</th>
        <th>Description</th>
        <th>Retail Price</th>
        <th>Serving Size</th>
        <th>Brand Name</th>
      </tr>
      <!-- Create a for loop to display all the data from the database in a format similar to this -->
       <% for (let i = 0; i < hummus.length; i++)
       { %>
        <tr>
          <td><%= hummus[i].name %></td>
          <td><%= hummus[i].description %></td>
          <td><%= hummus[i].retailprice %></td>
          <td><%= hummus[i].servingsize %></td>
          <td><%= hummus[i].brandname %></td>
        </tr>
       <%}%>
    </table>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
